The angle bisectors AD and CE divide angle BAC into three angles: angle BAD, angle DAC, and angle ECA. Since AD and CE are angle bisectors, we know that angle BAD = angle DAC = x and angle ECA = 88/2 = 44 degrees.

We can use the triangle ACE to find angle x. We know that angle ACE = 44 degrees and angle ECA = 44 degrees, so angle EAC = 180 - 44 - 44 = 92 degrees.

Now, we can use the triangle ABD to find angle x. We know that angle BAD = x and angle ABD = 90 - 88 = 2 degrees, so angle ADB = 180 - x - 2 = 180 - 92 = 88 degrees.

Therefore, angle x = 88 degrees.

